or, and General Jaeger play an intense game of \"Old Man\", an improvisation of old maid. They all mention references to their victories; Gregor and Jaeger quickly make their exit for the round. All that remains is Selvaria and Maximillan, where Selvaria cannot get rid of her affection for Maximillan. In a desperate attempt to prevent her from losing the game, she moves her hand around in almost unconscious fashion. She ends up losing, but they continue to play until the next morning, with Maximillan not paying any attention to the time...\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| Title               = Be On Guard in the Girls' Bath!\n| NativeTitle         = \u30ac\u30fc\u30eb\u30ba\u30fb\u30d0\u30fc\u30b9\u3067\u30ac\u30fc\u30c9\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = \n| ShortSummary        = Marina, Alicia, Edy, Rosie, and Susie are taking a hot bath in a private tent. Everyone prepares to leave until Captain Varrot suddenly appears in front of them, asking everybody to remain in the bath longer. As everybody remains silent with the captain, Varrot talks about Largo, who worked in the same company in the first Europan War. She talks about how Largo would often be turned down by her. Due to Largo's passion for vegetables, he would use vegetable flowers instead of roses... and then continue to discuss where those flowers came from...and then how cute she was holding one of the flowers... and then everybody passes out from being in the hot bath too long...\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| Title               = Rebirth! Squad 7\n| NativeTitle         = \u518d\u751f\uff01 \u5206\u968a7\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = \n| ShortSummary        = At the Gallian Military Base, Captain Varrot gazes outside of the window with her eyes closed...only to look back at Squad 7 with Hans' pig ears... They start speaking ~buhii~ as the main communication language.. All of Squad 7 stands at attention with each character having the same pig ears. Hans makes his entrance strapped to Alicia, speaking Japanese orders to the rest of the crew... only to have the rest of the squad answer ~buhii~ in agreement. All discussions are comprehended in ~buhii~ (fortunately a japanese translation of the dialogue is present). All of Squad 7 praises Hans for his decisive efforts to keep Squad 7 in top form...\nOnly to appear as an awkward dream for a sleeping Hans...\n}} \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 8\n| Title               = Cordelia's Secret!\n| NativeTitle         = \u30b3\u30fc\u30c7\u30ea\u30a2\u306e\u79d8\u5bc6\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = \n| ShortSummary        = Princess Cordelia contemplates to herself about meeting Lt. Welkin for the first time in a long while. She tries to surprise him...using a collection of headgear. She starts off with Gekota, then to a lizard, to bunny ears, cat headgear, and so on. After trying on various headgears, she falls asleep only to be late for her English fluency exam. As she runs to make her exam, her waitress casually greets her...only to realize something's odd...and to see Maurtis von Borg wear her crown...and realize that he is bald after seeing a wig right beside him...\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 9\n| Title               = Vowing Eternity (Epilogue)\n| NativeTitle         = \u8a93\u3044\u306e\u6c38\u9060\uff08\u30a8\u30d4\u30ed\u30fc\u30b0\uff09\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = \n| ShortSummary        = The episode starts with a letter from Alicia to Susie. Alicia narrates about how all the Squad 7 members are and what the members are doing after the war. She also mentions how she has to put off the marriage ceremony until she and Welkin finish respective university exams. As Alicia and Welkin poke fun at each other in Bruhl, Largo and Rosie make an unexpected visit, as well as the rest of Squad 7. They all congratulate Alicia and Welkin on their engagement, along with suggesting them to hold the marriage ceremony right away. A very makeshift wedding gown is made, and the couple become officially married in the sunset...\n}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n* [http://www.valkyria-anime.com/oa/index.html Official Valkyria Chronicles TV episode guide {{in lang|ja}}]\n\n{{Valkyria series}}\n{{Portal|Anime and manga}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of anime episodes|Valkyria Chronicles]]\n[[Category:Valkyria Chronicles|Episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Valkyria Chronicles'' episodes}}\n[[File:Valkyria Chronicles DVD Volume 1.jpg|right|thumb|200px|''Valkyria Chronicles'' DVD cover of volume 1, released in Japan. Welkin Gunther and Alicia Melchiott, the protagonists of the first ''Valkyria Chronicles'', are featured on the cover.]]\n''Valkyria Chronicles'' is an [[anime]] series loosely based on the [[Sega]] video game ''[[Valkyria Chronicles]]''. It began broadcasting on April 4, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allcinema.net/prog/show_c.php?num_c=333392|script-title=ja:\u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2|language=Japanese|accessdate=2009-04-08|publisher=All Cinema}}</ref> The show is produced by [[Aniplex]]'s [[A-1 Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.dengeki.com/elem/000/000/120/120894/|title=\u300c\u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2\u300d\u304c2009\u5e74\u6625\u306bTV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u5316! \u5236\u4f5c\u306fA-1 Pictures!!|accessdate=2008-11-12|date=2008-11-12|publisher=Dengeki Online}}</ref><ref name=\"ANN\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2008-11-12/valkyria-chronicles-game-to-get-tv-anime-next-spring|title=Valkyria Chronicles Game to Get TV Anime Next Spring|accessdate=2008-11-12|date=2008-11-12|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> The series is directed by Yasutaka Yamamoto<ref name=\"MBS\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mbs.jp/valkyria/|title=Official Valkyria Chronicles MBS Page|accessdate=2009-07-08|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"Cast and Staff\">{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/staff/index.html|title=Official Valkyria Chronicles Cast/Staff Page|accessdate=2009-04-19|language=Japanese}}</ref> and written by [[Michiko Yokote]] under the Project Valkyria Group.<ref name=\"MBS\"/><ref name=\"Cast and Staff\"/> ''Valkyria Chronicles'' aired on [[Animax]], [[Tokyo MX]], [[Mainichi Broadcasting System|MBS]], [[Chubu-Nippon Broadcasting|CBC]], [[Chiba Television Broadcasting|Chiba TV]],<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090423013346/http://akibanana.com/?q=node%2F1470 |archivedate=April 23, 2009 |url=http://www.akibanana.com/?q=node/1470 |title=Valkyria Chronicles Anime Series Begins in April |date=2009-02-18 |accessdate=2015-11-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Television Kanagawa]], [[Television Hokkaido]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]] and [[TVQ Kyushu Broadcasting]].<ref name=\"TAF\">{{cite web|url=http://akibanana.com/?q=node/1588|title=Chronicles of Valkyria Anime Starts Broadcast Run in April!|date=2009-03-29|accessdate=2009-04-19}}</ref>\n\nSet during the Second Europan War between The Autocratic East Europan Imperial Alliance and Atlantic Federation, the plot focuses on the Gallian Front fought between the Empire and The Principality of Gallia. Welkin Gunther, a college student and son of the First Europan War hero General Belgen Gunther, Isara Gunther, a brilliant Darcsen mechanic and Welkin's foster sister, and Alicia Melchiott, a baker and member of the Bruhl Townwatch, get involved in the war when the Imperials invade Gallia to secure its rich Ragnite deposits. After managing to escape their hometown Bruhl after the Imperials captured it, the three of them join Squad 7 of the Gallian Militia to help free their country from the Empire.\n\nThe theme song, {{nihongo|\"Asu e no Kizuna\"|\u660e\u65e5\u3078\u306e\u30ad\u30ba\u30ca||lit. \"The Bonds that Lead to Tomorrow\"}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/special/movie/090324pv_m.html|title=TV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3 \u300c\u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2\u300d \u30d7\u30ed\u30e2\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa|language=Japanese|accessdate=2009-04-08}}</ref> is performed by [[Himeka|Catherine St. Onge]], as winner of the [[Animax Anison Grand Prix]] competition, under her chosen moniker of Himeka; the original score for the anime is composed and conducted by the game's composer [[Hitoshi Sakimoto]].<ref name=\"mainichi3\">{{cite web|url=http://mainichi.jp/enta/mantan/news/20090226mog00m200037000c.html |title=HIMEKA: \u300c\u79c1\u306f\u97f3\u697d\u3068\u7d50\u5a5a\u3057\u307e\u3059\u300d \u30ab\u30ca\u30c0\u51fa\u8eab\"\u30a2\u30cb\u30bd\u30f3\u754c\u306e\u9ed2\u8239\"\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u4f1a\u898b |publisher=[[Mainichi Shimbun]] |date=2009-02-26 |accessdate=2009-03-06 |language=Japanese |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090301100407/http://mainichi.jp/enta/mantan/news/20090226mog00m200037000c.html |archivedate=2009-03-01 }}</ref><ref name=\"yahoo3\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302033253/http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20090226-00000010-maiall-ent|archivedate=March 2, 2009|url=http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20090226-00000010-maiall-ent|title=<HIMEKA>\u300c\u79c1\u306f\u97f3\u697d\u3068\u7d50\u5a5a\u3057\u307e\u3059\u300d \u30ab\u30ca\u30c0\u51fa\u8eab\"\u30a2\u30cb\u30bd\u30f3\u754c\u306e\u9ed2\u8239\"\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u4f1a\u898b|work=Mainichi Shimbun|publisher=[[Yahoo! Japan]]|date=2009-02-26|accessdate=2009-03-06|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"ann-anison\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-02-18/canada-st-onge-to-sing-valkyria-anime-theme-song|title=Canada's St. Onge to Sing Valkyria Anime's Theme Song|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2009-02-18|accessdate=2009-03-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animecenter.jp/eng/200904/05154516.php|title=Chronicles of Valkyria Anime Starts Broadcast Run in April!|date=2009-04-05|accessdate=2009-04-19|publisher=[[Tokyo Anime Center]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090423053221/http://www.animecenter.jp/eng/200904/05154516.php|archive-date=2009-04-23|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her CD single has been released on May 27, 2009.<ref name=\"OCD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/dvdcd/cd.html|title=CD Single section, Official Valkryia Chronicles DVD/CD Page|accessdate=2009-07-01|language=Japanese}}</ref> The ending theme, {{nihongo|\"Ano Kaze ni Notte\"|\u30a2\u30ce\u98a8\u30cb\u30ce\u30c3\u30c6}} is sung by the band [[PE'Z|pe'zmoku]] with a CD single released on May 27, 2009; the special version features a cover of Welkin, Alicia and Faldio.<ref name=\"OCD\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinra.net/news/2009/04/02/130205.php|title=pe'zmoku, \u82e6\u96e3\u3092\u4e57\u308a\u8d8a\u3048\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u300c\u30a2\u30ce\u98a8\u30cb\u30ce\u30c3\u30c6\u300d\u304c\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u6c7a\u5b9a|accessdate=2009-04-19|language=Japanese}}</ref> The second theme song, {{nihongo|\"Kanashimi Rensa\"|\u30ab\u30ca\u30b7\u30df\u30ec\u30f3\u30b5}}, is sung by [[Maria (band)|Maria]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/news/index.html|title=\u4eca\u9031\u672b\u3088\u308a\u65b0\u30af\u30fc\u30eb\u7a81\u5165\uff01\u65b0OP\u5834\u9762\u30ab\u30c3\u30c8\u516c\u958b\uff01|accessdate=2009-07-06|date=2009-07-02|language=Japanese}}</ref> that starts episode 14.<ref name=\"New\">{{cite web|url=http://theakiba.com/2009/07/05/valkyria-chronicles-new-op-ed-preview/|title=Valkyria Chronicles New OP ED Preview|accessdate=2009-07-07|date=2009-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090707232729/http://theakiba.com/2009/07/05/valkyria-chronicles-new-op-ed-preview/|archive-date=2009-07-07|url-status=dead}}</ref> The second ending song, {{nihongo|\"Hitotsu no Negai\"|\u3072\u3068\u3064\u306e\u9858\u3044}}, is sung by Hikari Inoue<ref name=\"New\"/> beginning from episode 14 until episode 25. Episode 26's ending song is \"Brightest Morning\", which is also performed by Inoue. CD singles for Kanashimi Rensa and Hitotsu no Negai were released on August 12, 2009 and August 5, 2009.<ref name=\"New\"/> A ''Valkyria Chronicles'' drama CD was released on July 24, 2009 with another on October 7, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/dvdcd/cd_d.html|title=Drama CD, Official Valkyria Chronicles DVD/CD Page|accessdate=2009-07-01|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nNine [[DVD region code|Region 2 DVDs]] of ''Valkyria Chronicles'' were released, with volume 1 released on August 5, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/dvdcd/dvd01.html|script-title=ja:\u300c\u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 1\u300d|accessdate=2009-07-01|language=Japanese}}</ref> Volume 2 was released on September 2, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/dvdcd/dvd02.html|script-title=ja:\u300c\u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 2\u300d|accessdate=2009-08-21|language=Japanese}}</ref> Volume 3 was released on October 7, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valkyria-anime.com/dvdcd/dvd03.html|script-title=ja:\u300c\u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 3\u300d|accessdate=2009-08-21|language=Japanese}}</ref> Volume 4 was released on November 4, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/switch-language/product/B002I8ODBE?language=en_JP|title=Amazon.co.jp - \u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 4 [DVD] DVD\u30fb\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30ec\u30a4 - \u5343\u8449\u9032\u6b69, \u4e95\u4e0a\u9ebb\u91cc\u5948, \u5c71\u672c\u9756\u8cb4|work=amazon.co.jp|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> Volume 5 was released on December 12, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B002ORL9DO|title=Amazon.co.jp - \u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 5 [DVD] DVD\u30fb\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30ec\u30a4 - \u5343\u8449\u9032\u6b69, \u4e95\u4e0a\u9ebb\u91cc\u5948, \u5c71\u672c\u9756\u8cb4|work=amazon.co.jp|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> Volume 6 was released January 13, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B002OUQKZI|title=Amazon.co.jp - \u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 6 [DVD] DVD\u30fb\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30ec\u30a4 - \u5343\u8449\u9032\u6b69, \u4e95\u4e0a\u9ebb\u91cc\u5948, \u5c71\u672c\u9756\u8cb4|work=amazon.co.jp|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> Volume 7 was released on February 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B002TJBATK|title=Amazon.co.jp - \u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 7 [DVD] DVD\u30fb\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30ec\u30a4 - \u5343\u8449\u9032\u6b69, \u4e95\u4e0a\u9ebb\u91cc\u5948, \u5c71\u672c\u9756\u8cb4|work=amazon.co.jp|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> Volume 8 was released on March 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B002TJBAU4|title=Amazon.co.jp - \u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 8 [DVD] DVD\u30fb\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30ec\u30a4 - \u5343\u8449\u9032\u6b69, \u4e95\u4e0a\u9ebb\u91cc\u5948, \u5c71\u672c\u9756\u8cb4|work=amazon.co.jp|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> Volume 9 was released on April 7, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B002TJBAUE|title=Amazon.co.jp - \u6226\u5834\u306e\u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30ad\u30e5\u30ea\u30a2 9 [DVD] DVD\u30fb\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30ec\u30a4 - \u5343\u8449\u9032\u6b69, \u4e95\u4e0a\u9ebb\u91cc\u5948, \u5c71\u672c\u9756\u8cb4|work=amazon.co.jp|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Valkyria Chronicles Episode List==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:98%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n! style=\"width:3%;\"  | No.\n! Title\n! style=\"width:12%;\" | Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = Encounter and Battle\n| TranslitTitle       = Senka no Deai\n| NativeTitle         = \u6226\u706b\u306e\u51fa\u4f1a\u3044\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|4|4}}\n| ShortSummary        = Under threat of an approaching Imperial invasion, the inhabitants of Bruhl are forced to evacuate under the protection and assistance of the Bruhl Townwatch. Alicia, a member of the Townwatch, arrests Welkin Gunther at gunpoint on suspicion of espionage, despite his protestations of innocence. Welkin manages to escape and Alicia, still convinced that he is an Imperial spy, gives chase. During the chase, both of them are spotted by Imperial scouts and fired upon. The two retreat to the safety of the Gunther estate in the Bruhl countryside, where they meet up with Welkin's Darcsen foster-sister Isara. Imperial troops and tanks arrive and surround the estate.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| Title               = Prayer of the Edelweiss Dandelion\n| TranslitTitle       = Konayukis\u014d no Inori\n| NativeTitle         = \u30b3\u30ca\u30e6\u30ad\u30bd\u30a6\u306e\u7948\u308a\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|4|11}}\n| ShortSummary        = Welkin, Isara, and Alicia manage to escape using the prototype tank Edelweiss, which was designed and built by Isara's biological father, a Darcsen engineer. They flee to Bruhl, with the Imperial forces in close pursuit. The Bruhl Townwatch has to delay the Imperials to allow the evacuation to proceed unhindered and hold out until the Regular Army arrives; however, they are handicapped by their lack of combat experience and poorly maintained equipment and suffer badly. In the Edelweiss, Welkin and Isara attack the invading Imperial troops and tanks to give the remaining Townwatch members the necessary time to escape from Bruhl as the Gallian Regular Army reaches the outskirts of Bruhl. However, even though they arrive in time to rescue the civilians, the Regular Army decides against retaking Bruhl from the superior Imperial force. Due to the capture of Bruhl by the Imperials, Alicia and her friend Susie Evans enlist in the Gallian Militia. Alicia is later surprised to find out that Welkin has also joined the Militia.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| Title               = The Birth of Squad Seven\n| TranslitTitle       = Dainana Sh\u014dtai Tanj\u014d\n| NativeTitle         = \u7b2c7\u5c0f\u968a\u8a95\u751f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|4|18}}\n| ShortSummary        = Welkin is promoted to the rank of Lieutenant and assigned as commander of Squad 7 with Alicia as his Sergeant and second in command, much to her dismay. They encounter Faldio Landzaat, an old college friend of Welkin's who has been appointed commander of Squad 1. Welkin introduces himself to Squad 7 but his new subordinates treat him with disdain as they believe, correctly, that he is naive and inexperienced. Squad 7 sets off for Vasel Bridge, which connects the main road to the capital city of Randgriz, and is under Imperials control. When certain members of Squad voice objections about the presence of Isara in the group because she is a Darcsen, Welkin makes a bet with them that if he and Squad 7 manages to retake the bridge in two days, they have to accept his command and Isara's continued presence. The following morning, using fog as cover, the Edelweiss dives into the river and reaches the other side in a surprise attack allowing Squad 7 to capture the bridge. After the battle, most of the Squad 7 have accepted Welkin with the exception of Rosie who adamantly refuses to acknowledge Isara.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| Title               = A Brief Day Off\n| TranslitTitle       = Tsukanoma no Ky\u016bjitsu\n| NativeTitle         = \u675f\u306e\u9593\u306e\u4f11\u65e5\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|4|25}}\n| ShortSummary        = Faldio attempts to socialize with Alicia with mixed results. Despite the success of Squad 7 in capturing the Vasel Bridge from the Imperials, General Damon of the Gallian Regular Army remains disdainful of the Militia, and chooses to exclude Squad 7 from participation in an assault on a vital Imperial supply base in Kloden, leading to widespread resentment from the Militia. Alicia is troubled by Welkin's quiet acceptance of General Damon's implicit insult, but Faldio seizes the chance to encourage her to have more faith in Welkin. Damon is defeated by General Gregor of the Imperial Army and Squad 7 is then ordered to attack Kloden, with support from Faldio's Squad 1.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| Title               = Assault on Kloden\n| TranslitTitle       = Kur\u014dden Kish\u016bsen\n| NativeTitle         = \u30af\u30ed\u30fc\u30c7\u30f3\u5947\u8972\u6226\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|5|2}}\n| ShortSummary        = Welkin and Squad 7 team up with Faldio and Squad 1 to attack the heavily defended Kloden supply base, held by General Gregor. When Rosie captures a porcavian (a winged pig), leading to the discovery of an animal trail, Welkin proposes using the Edelweiss and Squad 7 led by Rosie and Largo to distract the main Imperial force while Alicia, Faldio and Squad 1 sneak into the base from the side using the animal trail, much to Alicia's dismay as she is not fond of Faldio. Advancing aggressively, Alicia is shot during the operation, but Faldio is able to help her to safety. However, she soon resumes fighting as her wound has healed quickly, much to the amazement of Faldio. The Gallian attack proves irresistible and Jaeger arrives with Imperial reinforcements to assist the reluctant Gregor in escaping. The Militia captures the base, but Welkin has to restrain Faldio from pursuing the retreating Imperials. After the battle, Alicia decides to keep the porcavian as a mascot and names it Hans.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| Title               = War Correspondent, Fight on!\n| TranslitTitle       = J\u016bgun Kisha, Funt\u014d su!\n| NativeTitle         = \u5f93\u8ecd\u8a18\u8005, \u596e\u95d8\u3059!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|5|9}}\n| ShortSummary        = War correspondent Irene Ellet arrives to interview Lieutenant Welkin Gunther for her radio show hosted by Radio GBS. However, Alicia is worried that Welkin, being absentminded and unorthodox in the way he handles things, may end up saying things that might tarnish the reputation of the Militia so she interferes with Welkin's interview, clashing with Irene repeatedly. After not being able to get useful information from Welkin's subordinates, Irene finally manages to corner Welkin in the men's bathroom, which leads to hilarity when Alicia storms in. Squad 7 celebrates with a barbecue courtesy of Irene, but a brawl breaks out between Squad 7 and Squad 1, until everyone settles down and emerges as friends. Irene finally gets her interview and figures out why Alicia was being so overprotective. To Alicia's relief, Irene's broadcast praises Squad 7, though she protests vehemently when Irene wants another interview.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| Title               = Darcsen Calamity\n| TranslitTitle       = Darukusu no Saiyaku\n| NativeTitle         = \u30c0\u30eb\u30af\u30b9\u306e\u707d\u5384\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2009|5|16}}\n| ShortSummary        = In an attempt to belittle the Gallian Militia's recent accomplishments compared to the Regular Army, General Damon assigns the Militia to the Barious Desert, over the protests of Captain Varrot. Welkin and Faldio debate the nature of the Darcsen Calamity and whether any of the legends represent what truly happened. The two Militia officers head out to visit the Valkyrur Ruins with Alicia, Ramal, and Isara but their jeep breaks down due to mechanical failure. While Welkin, Faldio 